description:
Responsibilities

Overseeing, coordinating and taking the lead role in providing compliance and market risk advice and support to the investment teams on various day to day matters;
Developing and maintaining various programs to ensure adherence to investment mandate and risk control policies;
Ensure achievement of all requirements for risk and compliance reporting and escalation of risks as required;
Ensure adherence to risk management frameworks through effective implementation of a consistent enterprise risk and control management regime across the company;
Building strong relationships with portfolio managers to have risk discussions and facilitate risk management framework implementation including:- promoting awareness of risk and risk management best practices, and as needed, working with and advising portfolio managers in developing effective mitigation steps and controls, analyzing and reporting firm level risk themes, risk levels and focus action items.

Requirement

Master or above with good school/academic records;
Working experience in financial industry would be an advantage;
A good team player with good communication and interpersonal skill;
Strong analytical minds with solid execution skills;
Excellent command of written and spoken English and Putonghua;
Possess of programing skills of at least one of following: SQL, Python, R, C, C#;
Fresh graduate will also be considered.

We offer an attractive remuneration with excellent opportunities to the right candidate. Interested parties please apply with detailed resume. (All personal information received will be kept in strictly confidential and only for recruitment purpose only.)

Responsibilities



Develop and enhance risk models that measure investment risk exposures, and provide compliance and risk management advice to the investment teams;
Initiate or participate in data analytics and research projects to systematically track index rebalances, factor performance, corporate actions and other investment related topics;
Ensure achievement of all requirements for risk and compliance reporting and escalation of risks as required;
Work closely with colleagues from portfolio management, research, and IT and facilitate benchmark and risk management framework implementation.

Requirement


Bachelor or above in quantitative fields with good school/academic records;
Working experience in financial industry and/or data analytics areas would be an advantage;
Possess of programing skills of SQL, Python, R, C# would be preferred;
Experience in using Bloomberg, FactSet and Capital IQ is an advantage;
Experience in index/quantitative research/corporate actions is a plus;
A good team player with good communication and interpersonal skill;
Strong analytical minds with solid execution skills;
Excellent command of written and spoken English and Mandarin;
Fresh graduate will also be considered.

We offer an attractive remuneration with excellent opportunities to the right candidate. Interested parties please apply with detailed resume. (All personal information received will be kept in strictly confidential and only for recruitment purpose only.)

Responsibilities:
To assist drafting the Group’s integrated risk management report;

To assist drafting risk management policies;

To assist drafting the Group’s risk management strategies and annual work plan;

To coordinate the consolidation of risk management information from various risk management units;

To coordinate implementing risk management projects;

To keep track of changes in macro economies, regulatory requirements and business development, analyze its impact on risk management, and propose risk management measures accordingly.

Requirements:
Qualifications of degree or above, major in Economics, Finance, Accounting, Business & Administration or relevant professions.

Working experience of 5 years or above in bank with at least 2 years in risk management, such as credit risk, market risk, interest risk.

Excellent analytical, problem solving, communication and language skills.

Familiar with MS Office software, such as MS Word, Excel and PowerPoint.

Excellent Chinese and English.

We offer competitive remuneration package and comprehensive fringe benefits including medical and life insurance, and different types of allowances to the right candidate. Interested parties, please submit your application online. For details, please visit our website http://www.bochk.com

[via APPLY NOW]  

