Responsibilities:


Act as department head to manage various teams to meet all operation and compliance requirements;
Manage centralization and transactional services for retail and corporate customers;
Support Chief Operating Officer to develop centralised operations for Head Office and Mainland;
Handle time critical customer transactions (including time deposit, transfer, unit trust operations, payment services, complicated problem solving, customer instructions handling);
Develop departmental procedure manuals/guidelines and policy, including split office operations, BCP;
Maintain MIS and compilation of various reports; and manage budgeting ;
Handle AML and all regulatory reporting;
Manage Key strategic projects; and
Ad hoc tasks/projects as assigned 

Requirements


University graduate in Business Administration or related disciplines;
Minimum 15 years solid experience in retail banking or back-office operations with at least 6 - 8 years as department head level;
Solid experience in branch operations, payment operations, retail investment settlement and account opening;
Exposure in project management, especially in leading bank-wide projects;
Good communication and leading skills;
Project management skills; and AML handling knowledge;
Strong self-motivation with ability to work under pressure; and
Excellent analytical and with good command of both spoken and written English and Chinese including Putonghua.

We offer competitive remuneration package and promising career opportunities to the successful candidates. Interested parties, please send full resume with current & expected salary and the date of availability to The HR Division by clicking "Apply Now" button below. Please quote reference on your application. Information provided will be treated in strict confidence and only be used for recruitment purposes. Personal data of unsuccessful applications will be destroyed 24 months after the completion of the recruitment and selection exercise.

Responsibilities:

Follow up latest regulatory requirements and provide advisory services on compliance related issues in order to ensure business units in compliance with regulatory requirements;
Perform review on general compliance issues and monitor business compliance with relevant external regulatory requirements;
Assist in the formulating and executing compliance assurance projects;
Identify any deficiencies in business activities & operations during assurance reviews; and make recommendations to business units in improving & reinforcing compliance standards accordingly;
Monitor the implementation status of assurance review recommendations as agreed with units;
Compile compliance review reports and manage the reporting /escalation of review result to management;
Coordinate with Regulators and relevant internal stakeholders in handling Regulatory examination related requests;
Conduct compliance training when necessary; and
Perform other ad hoc projects or assignments.
Requirements:
University degree in Law, Business Administration, Finance or related discipline;
Minimum of 5 years’ solid experience in general regulatory compliance of which 4 years in investment and insurance compliance;
Sound knowledge of investment products such as securities, funds and bonds;
Conversant with banking rules and regulations including Banking Ordinance and Securities & Futures Ordinance;
Keep abreast of HKMA circulars, industry news and market information;
Excellent communication and interpersonal skills, able to work with stakeholders at different levels; and
Well-versed in spoken and written English and Chinese, including Putonghua.
We offer competitive remuneration package and promising career opportunities to the successful candidates. Interested parties, please send full resume with current & expected salary and the date of availability to The HR Division by clicking "Apply Now" button below. Please quote reference on your application. Information provided will be treated in strict confidence and only be used for recruitment purposes. Personal data of unsuccessful applications will be destroyed 24 months after the completion of the recruitment and selection exercise.

Duties and Responsibilities

Monitor and analyse debtor (airline)’s credit related matters, such as historical financial and business performance, timely prepare draft report to Risk Management Department, senior management and other relevant departments in case of debtor’s credit deterioration;
Maintain and update airlines credit rating table;
Monitor and analyse macro economy, geopolitical risks, aviation industry, financial market and conduct deep-dive research to specific risks when required;
Monitor the Company’s operating asset;
Draft and update Risk Management Department’s relevant policies and procedures;
Perform initial review on the assessment of the Company’s operational risk, maintain risk register, and monitor the implementation status on risk mitigation strategies by relevant departments and prepare draft report to senior management;
Conduct internal control review, draft internal control review report, and monitor the mitigation actions of internal control review observations;
Other relevant tasks assigned by the Company or Risk Management Department.
Qualifications

Bachelor and/or above degree in business administration, accounting, finance or other related majors.
3+ years of risk management, business, accounting or finance experience.
Strong analytical and logical skills;
Strong interpersonal, verbal and written communication skills, be able to work efficiently and effectively with other stakeholders;
Clear, accurate and concise writing skills;
Fast learner, strong team player, self-motivated, detail-oriented, multi-tasking skills with strong ability of time management and be able to meet deadlines under pressure;
roficiency in maths and knowledge in accounting;
Familiar with Microsoft Office Suite for financial, credit and portfolio analysis and drawing up documents;
Strong command of written and spoken English (Japanese is not required but will be an advantage).
*All information collected will be used for recruitment purpose only.

Job Responsibilities

Conduct customer due diligence/enhanced due diligence reviews and research for clients, as part of the firm's AML/CFT Compliance program;
Analysis of accounts and client information according to prescribed internal control policies and procedures;
Identification and production of information required to satisfy Amber KYC due diligence policies and processes;
Develop, maintain, review and enhance AML & compliance related policies and procedures as well as proper control to ensure that the Bank's activities are in compliance with the latest regulatory requirements;

Requirements

Bachelor's degree with major in Business Administration or related disciplines
3-5 years' experience in undertaking AML / KYC reviews within a financial institution;
Working knowledge of AML, regulatory compliance and controls within the banking, financial services or fintech;
Good understanding of AML Compliance functions including KYC/CDD.
Strong stakeholder management skills. Strong teamwork, organizational, complex problem resolution and initiative;
Good command of both written and spoken English and Chinese.

